{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["58-HEB-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"HEB"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Hebrews \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Letter to the Hebrews \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Hebrews \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Heb \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["The Letter to the Hebrews \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"HEB 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 1:1"},"Allah, having in the past spoken to the fathers through the prophets at many times and in various ways,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 1:2"},"has at the end of these days spoken to us by his Son, whom he appointed heir of all things, through whom also he made the\nworlds. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 1:3"},"His Son is the radiance of his glory, the very image of his substance, and upholding all things by the word of his power,\nwho, when he had by himself purified us of our sins, sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 1:4"},"having become as much better than the angels as the more excellent name he has inherited is better than theirs.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 1:5"},"For to which of the angels did he say at any time, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You are my Son. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Today I have become your father?”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 2:7"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["and again, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will be to him a Father, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and he will be to me a Son?”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Samuel 7:14;\n1 Chronicles 17:13"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 1:6"},"When he again brings in the firstborn into the world he says, “Let all the angels of Allah worship\nhim.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 32:43 LXX"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 1:7"},"Of the angels he says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“He makes his angels winds, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and his servants a flame of fire.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 104:4"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 1:8"},"But of the Son he says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Your throne, O Allah, is forever and ever. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The sceptre of uprightness is the sceptre of your Kingdom. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 1:9"},"You have loved righteousness and hated iniquity; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["therefore Allah, your Allah, has anointed you with the oil of gladness above your\nfellows.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 45:6-7"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 1:10"},"And, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You, Lord, in the beginning, laid the foundation of the earth.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The heavens are the works of your hands. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 1:11"},"They will perish, but you continue. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They all will grow old like a garment does. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 1:12"},"You will roll them up like a mantle, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will be changed; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but you are the same. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your years won’t fail.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 102:25-27"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 1:13"},"But which of the angels has he told at any time, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Sit at my right hand, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until I make your enemies the footstool of your feet?”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:13\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 110:1"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 1:14"},"Aren’t they all serving spirits, sent out to do service for the sake of those who will inherit salvation?\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"HEB 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 2:1"},"Therefore we ought to pay greater attention to the things that were heard, lest perhaps we drift away.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 2:2"},"For if the word spoken through angels proved steadfast, and every transgression and disobedience received a just penalty,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 2:3"},"how will we escape if we neglect so great a salvation—which at the first having been spoken through the Lord, was\nconfirmed to us by those who heard, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 2:4"},"Allah also testifying with them, both by signs and wonders, by various works of power and by gifts of the Holy Spirit,\naccording to his own will? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 2:5"},"For he didn’t subject the world to come, of which we speak, to angels.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 2:6"},"But one has somewhere testified, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“What is man, that you think of him? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Or the son of man, that you care for him? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 2:7"},"You made him a little lower than the angels. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You crowned him with glory and honour.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “and set him over the works of your\nhands”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 2:8"},"You have put all things in subjection under his feet.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 8:4-6 "]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For in that he subjected all things to him, he left nothing that is not subject to him. But now we don’t see all things\nsubjected to him, yet. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 2:9"},"But we see him who has been made a little lower than the angels, Isa, because of the suffering of death crowned with glory\nand honour, that by the grace of Allah he should taste of death for everyone.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 2:10"},"For it became him, for whom are all things, and through whom are all things, in bringing many children to glory, to make\nthe author of their salvation perfect through sufferings. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 2:11"},"For both he who sanctifies and those who are sanctified are all from one, for which cause he is not ashamed to call them\nbrothers,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “brothers” here and where context allows may also be correctly translated “brothers\nand sisters” or “siblings.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 2:12"},"saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will declare your name to my brothers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Amongst the congregation I will sing your praise.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:12\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 22:22"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 2:13"},"Again, “I will put my trust in him.” Again, “Behold, here I am with the children whom Allah has given\nme.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 8:18"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 2:14"},"Since then the children have shared in flesh and blood, he also himself in the same way partook of the same, that through\ndeath he might bring to nothing him who had the power of death, that is, the Iblis,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 2:15"},"and might deliver all of them who through fear of death were all their lifetime subject to bondage.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 2:16"},"For most certainly, he doesn’t give help to angels, but he gives help to the\noffspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," of Ibrahim. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 2:17"},"Therefore he was obligated in all things to be made like his brothers, that he might become a merciful and faithful high\npriest in things pertaining to Allah, to make atonement for the sins of the people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 2:18"},"For in that he himself has suffered being tempted, he is able to help those who are tempted.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"HEB 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 3:1"},"Therefore, holy brothers, partakers of a heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our confession: Isa,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 3:2"},"who was faithful to him who appointed him, as also Musa was in all his house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 3:3"},"For he has been counted worthy of more glory than Musa, because he who built the house has more honour than the house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 3:4"},"For every house is built by someone; but he who built all things is Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 3:5"},"Musa indeed was faithful in all his house as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were afterward to be spoken,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 3:6"},"but Masih is faithful as a Son over his house. We are his house, if we hold fast our confidence and the glorying of our\nhope firm to the end. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 3:7"},"Therefore, even as the Holy Spirit says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Today if you will hear his voice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 3:8"},"don’t harden your hearts, as in the rebellion, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like as in the day of the trial in the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 3:9"},"where your fathers tested me and tried me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and saw my deeds for forty years. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 3:10"},"Therefore I was displeased with that generation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and said, ‘They always err in their heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but they didn’t know my ways.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 3:11"},"As I swore in my wrath, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘They will not enter into my rest.’”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["3:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur\n95:7-11"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 3:12"},"Beware, brothers, lest perhaps there might be in any one of you an evil heart of unbelief, in falling away from the\nliving Allah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 3:13"},"but exhort one another day by day, so long as it is called “today”, lest any one of you be hardened by the deceitfulness\nof sin. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 3:14"},"For we have become partakers of Masih, if we hold the beginning of our confidence firm to the end,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 3:15"},"while it is said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Today if you will hear his voice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["don’t harden your hearts, as in the rebellion.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["3:15\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 95:7-8"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 3:16"},"For who, when they heard, rebelled? Wasn’t it all those who came out of Egypt led by Musa?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 3:17"},"With whom was he displeased forty years? Wasn’t it with those who sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 3:18"},"To whom did he swear that they wouldn’t enter into his rest, but to those who were disobedient?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 3:19"},"We see that they weren’t able to enter in because of unbelief.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"HEB 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 4:1"},"Let’s fear therefore, lest perhaps anyone of you should seem to have come short of a promise of entering into his rest.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 4:2"},"For indeed we have had good news preached to us, even as they also did, but the word they heard didn’t profit them,\nbecause it wasn’t mixed with faith by those who heard. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 4:3"},"For we who have believed do enter into that rest, even as he has said, “As I swore in my wrath, they will not enter into\nmy rest;”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 95:11 "]}],"caller":"+"}," although the works were finished from the foundation of the world.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 4:4"},"For he has said this somewhere about the seventh day, “Allah rested on the seventh day from all his\nworks;”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Genesis 2:2"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 4:5"},"and in this place again, “They will not enter into my rest.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 95:11"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 4:6"},"Seeing therefore it remains that some should enter into it, and they to whom the good news was preached before failed to\nenter in because of disobedience, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 4:7"},"he again defines a certain day, today, saying through Dawood so long a time afterward (just as has been said),\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Today if you will hear his voice, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["don’t harden your hearts.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["4:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 95:7-8"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 4:8"},"For if Joshua had given them rest, he would not have spoken afterward of another day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 4:9"},"There remains therefore a Sabbath rest for the people of Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 4:10"},"For he who has entered into his rest has himself also rested from his works, as Allah did from his.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 4:11"},"Let’s therefore give diligence to enter into that rest, lest anyone fall after the same example of disobedience.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 4:12"},"For the word of Allah is living and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing even to the dividing of soul\nand spirit, of both joints and marrow, and is able to discern the thoughts and intentions of the heart.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 4:13"},"There is no creature that is hidden from his sight, but all things are naked and laid open before the eyes of him to whom\nwe must give an account. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 4:14"},"Having then a great high priest who has passed through the heavens, Isa, the Son of Allah, let’s hold tightly to our\nconfession. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 4:15"},"For we don’t have a high priest who can’t be touched with the feeling of our infirmities, but one who has been in all\npoints tempted like we are, yet without sin. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 4:16"},"Let’s therefore draw near with boldness to the throne of grace, that we may receive mercy and may find grace for help in\ntime of need. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"HEB 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 5:1"},"For every high priest, being taken from amongst men, is appointed for men in things pertaining to Allah, that he may offer\nboth gifts and sacrifices for sins. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 5:2"},"The high priest can deal gently with those who are ignorant and going astray, because he himself is also surrounded with\nweakness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 5:3"},"Because of this, he must offer sacrifices for sins for the people, as well as for himself.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 5:4"},"Nobody takes this honour on himself, but he is called by Allah, just like Harun was.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 5:5"},"So also Masih didn’t glorify himself to be made a high priest, but it was he who said to him,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You are my Son. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Today I have become your father.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["5:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 2:7"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 5:6"},"As he says also in another place, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You are a priest forever, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["after the order of Melchizedek.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["5:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 110:4"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 5:7"},"He, in the days of his flesh, having offered up prayers and petitions with strong crying and tears to him who was able to\nsave him from death, and having been heard for his godly fear, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 5:8"},"though he was a Son, yet learnt obedience by the things which he suffered.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 5:9"},"Having been made perfect, he became to all of those who obey him the author of eternal salvation,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 5:10"},"named by Allah a high priest after the order of Melchizedek.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 5:11"},"About him we have many words to say, and hard to interpret, seeing you have become dull of hearing.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 5:12"},"For although by this time you should be teachers, you again need to have someone teach you the rudiments of the first\nprinciples of the revelations of Allah. You have come to need milk, and not solid food.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 5:13"},"For everyone who lives on milk is not experienced in the word of righteousness, for he is a baby.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 5:14"},"But solid food is for those who are full grown, who by reason of use have their senses exercised to discern good and\nevil. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"HEB 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 6:1"},"Therefore leaving the teaching of the first principles of Masih, let’s press on to perfection—not laying again a\nfoundation of repentance from dead works, of faith towards Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 6:2"},"of the teaching of baptisms, of laying on of hands, of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgement.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 6:3"},"This will we do, if Allah permits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 6:4"},"For concerning those who were once enlightened and tasted of the heavenly gift, and were made partakers of the Holy\nSpirit, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 6:5"},"and tasted the good word of Allah and the powers of the age to come,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 6:6"},"and then fell away, it is impossible to renew them again to repentance; seeing they crucify the Son of Allah for\nthemselves again, and put him to open shame. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 6:7"},"For the land which has drunk the rain that comes often on it and produces a crop suitable for them for whose sake it is\nalso tilled, receives blessing from Allah; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 6:8"},"but if it bears thorns and thistles, it is rejected and near being cursed, whose end is to be burnt.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 6:9"},"But, beloved, we are persuaded of better things for you, and things that accompany salvation, even though we speak like\nthis. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 6:10"},"For Allah is not unrighteous, so as to forget your work and the labour of love which you showed towards his name, in that\nyou served the saints, and still do serve them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 6:11"},"We desire that each one of you may show the same diligence to the fullness of hope even to the end,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 6:12"},"that you won’t be sluggish, but imitators of those who through faith and perseverance inherited the promises.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 6:13"},"For when Allah made a promise to Ibrahim, since he could swear by no one greater, he swore by himself,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 6:14"},"saying, “Surely blessing I will bless you, and multiplying I will multiply\nyou.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["6:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Genesis 22:17"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 6:15"},"Thus, having patiently endured, he obtained the promise. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 6:16"},"For men indeed swear by a greater one, and in every dispute of theirs the oath is final for confirmation.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 6:17"},"In this way Allah, being determined to show more abundantly to the heirs of the promise the immutability of his counsel,\ninterposed with an oath, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 6:18"},"that by two immutable things, in which it is impossible for Allah to lie, we may have a strong encouragement, who have\nfled for refuge to take hold of the hope set before us. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 6:19"},"This hope we have as an anchor of the soul, a hope both sure and steadfast and entering into that which is within the\nveil; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HEB 6:20"},"where as a forerunner Isa entered for us, having become a high priest forever after the order of Melchizedek.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"HEB 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 7:1"},"For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of Allah Most High, who met Ibrahim returning from the slaughter of the kings\nand blessed him, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 7:2"},"to whom also Ibrahim divided a tenth part of all (being first, by interpretation, “king of righteousness”, and then also\n“king of Salem”, which means “king of peace”, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 7:3"},"without father, without mother, without genealogy, having neither beginning of days nor end of life, but made like the Son\nof Allah), remains a priest continually. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 7:4"},"Now consider how great this man was, to whom even Ibrahim, the patriarch, gave a tenth out of the best plunder.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 7:5"},"They indeed of the sons of Levi who receive the priest’s office have a commandment to take tithes of the people according\nto the law, that is, of their brothers, though these have come out of the body of Ibrahim,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 7:6"},"but he whose genealogy is not counted from them has accepted tithes from Ibrahim, and has blessed him who has the\npromises. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 7:7"},"But without any dispute the lesser is blessed by the greater.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 7:8"},"Here people who die receive tithes, but there one receives tithes of whom it is testified that he lives.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 7:9"},"We can say that through Ibrahim even Levi, who receives tithes, has paid tithes,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 7:10"},"for he was yet in the body of his father when Melchizedek met him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 7:11"},"Now if perfection was through the Levitical priesthood (for under it the people have received the law), what further need\nwas there for another priest to arise after the order of Melchizedek, and not be called after the order of Harun?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 7:12"},"For the priesthood being changed, there is of necessity a change made also in the law.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 7:13"},"For he of whom these things are said belongs to another tribe, from which no one has officiated at the altar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 7:14"},"For it is evident that our Lord has sprung out of Judah, about which tribe Musa spoke nothing concerning priesthood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 7:15"},"This is yet more abundantly evident, if after the likeness of Melchizedek there arises another priest,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 7:16"},"who has been made, not after the law of a fleshly commandment, but after the power of an endless life;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 7:17"},"for it is testified, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You are a priest forever, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["according to the order of Melchizedek.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["7:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur\n110:4"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 7:18"},"For there is an annulling of a foregoing commandment because of its weakness and uselessness\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 7:19"},"(for the law made nothing perfect), and a bringing in of a better hope, through which we draw near to Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HEB 7:20"},"Inasmuch as he was not made priest without the taking of an oath\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"HEB 7:21"},"(for they indeed have been made priests without an oath), but he with an oath by him that says of him,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The Lord swore and will not change his mind, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘You are a priest forever, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["according to the order of Melchizedek.’”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["7:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur\n110:4"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"HEB 7:22"},"By so much, Isa has become the collateral of a better covenant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"HEB 7:23"},"Many, indeed, have been made priests, because they are hindered from continuing by death.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"HEB 7:24"},"But he, because he lives forever, has his priesthood unchangeable.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"HEB 7:25"},"Therefore he is also able to save to the uttermost those who draw near to Allah through him, seeing that he lives forever\nto make intercession for them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"HEB 7:26"},"For such a high priest was fitting for us: holy, guiltless, undefiled, separated from sinners, and made higher than the\nheavens; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"HEB 7:27"},"who doesn’t need, like those high priests, to offer up sacrifices daily, first for his own sins, and then for the sins of\nthe people. For he did this once for all, when he offered up himself.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"HEB 7:28"},"For the law appoints men as high priests who have weakness, but the word of the oath which came after the law appoints a\nSon forever who has been perfected. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"HEB 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 8:1"},"Now in the things which we are saying, the main point is this. We have such a high priest, who sat down on the right hand\nof the throne of the Majesty in the heavens, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 8:2"},"a servant of the sanctuary and of the true tabernacle, which the Lord pitched, not man.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 8:3"},"For every high priest is appointed to offer both gifts and sacrifices. Therefore it is necessary that this high priest\nalso have something to offer. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 8:4"},"For if he were on earth, he would not be a priest at all, seeing there are priests who offer the gifts according to the\nlaw, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 8:5"},"who serve a copy and shadow of the heavenly things, even as Musa was warned by Allah when he was about to make the\ntabernacle, for he said, “See, you shall make everything according to the pattern that was shown to you on the\nmountain.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 25:40"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 8:6"},"But now he has obtained a more excellent ministry, by so much as he is also the mediator of a better covenant, which on\nbetter promises has been given as law. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 8:7"},"For if that first covenant had been faultless, then no place would have been sought for a second.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 8:8"},"For finding fault with them, he said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “ἰδοὺ”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as\nan interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," the days come”, says the Lord, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“that I will make a new covenant with the house of Israel and with the house of Judah;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 8:9"},"not according to the covenant that I made with their fathers,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the day that I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land of Egypt;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for they didn’t continue in my covenant, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I disregarded them,” says the Lord. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 8:10"},"“For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["After those days,” says the Lord; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will put my laws into their mind, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will also write them on their heart. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will be their Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will be my people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 8:11"},"They will not teach every man his fellow citizen,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:11\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “neighbour” instead of “fellow citizen”"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every man his brother, saying, ‘Know the Lord,’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for all will know me, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from their least to their greatest. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 8:12"},"For I will be merciful to their unrighteousness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will remember their sins and lawless deeds no more.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["8:12\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 31:31-34"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 8:13"},"In that he says, “A new covenant”, he has made the first old. But that which is becoming old and grows aged is near to\nvanishing away. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"HEB 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 9:1"},"Now indeed even the first",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “tabernacle”"]}],"caller":"+"}," covenant had ordinances of divine service and an\nearthly sanctuary. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 9:2"},"For a tabernacle was prepared. In the first part were the lamp stand, the table, and the show bread; which is called the\nHoly Place. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 9:3"},"After the second veil was the tabernacle which is called the Holy of Holies,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 9:4"},"having a golden altar of incense, and the ark of the covenant overlaid on all sides with gold, in which was a golden pot\nholding the manna, Harun’s rod that budded, and the tablets of the covenant;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 9:5"},"and above it cherubim of glory overshadowing the mercy seat, of which things we can’t speak now in detail.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 9:6"},"Now these things having been thus prepared, the priests go in continually into the first tabernacle, accomplishing the\nservices, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 9:7"},"but into the second the high priest alone, once in the year, not without blood, which he offers for himself, and for the\nerrors of the people. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 9:8"},"The Holy Spirit is indicating this, that the way into the Holy Place wasn’t yet revealed while the first tabernacle was\nstill standing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 9:9"},"This is a symbol of the present age, where gifts and sacrifices are offered that are incapable, concerning the conscience,\nof making the worshipper perfect, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 9:10"},"being only (with meats and drinks and various washings) fleshly ordinances, imposed until a time of reformation.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 9:11"},"But Masih having come as a high priest of the coming good things, through the greater and more perfect tabernacle, not\nmade with hands, that is to say, not of this creation, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 9:12"},"nor yet through the blood of goats and calves, but through his own blood, entered in once for all into the Holy Place,\nhaving obtained eternal redemption. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 9:13"},"For if the blood of goats and bulls, and the ashes of a heifer sprinkling those who have been defiled, sanctify to the\ncleanness of the flesh, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 9:14"},"how much more will the blood of Masih, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself without defect to Allah, cleanse\nyour conscience from dead works to serve the living Allah? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 9:15"},"For this reason he is the mediator of a new covenant, since a death has occurred for the redemption of the transgressions\nthat were under the first covenant, that those who have been called may receive the promise of the eternal inheritance.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 9:16"},"For where a last will and testament is, there must of necessity be the death of him who made it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 9:17"},"For a will is in force where there has been death, for it is never in force while he who made it lives.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 9:18"},"Therefore even the first covenant has not been dedicated without blood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 9:19"},"For when every commandment had been spoken by Musa to all the people according to the law, he took the blood of the\ncalves and the goats, with water and scarlet wool and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book itself and all the people,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HEB 9:20"},"saying, “This is the blood of the covenant which Allah has commanded\nyou.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["9:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 24:8"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"HEB 9:21"},"Moreover he sprinkled the tabernacle and all the vessels of the ministry in the same way with the blood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"HEB 9:22"},"According to the law, nearly everything is cleansed with blood, and apart from shedding of blood there is no remission.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"HEB 9:23"},"It was necessary therefore that the copies of the things in the heavens should be cleansed with these, but the heavenly\nthings themselves with better sacrifices than these. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"HEB 9:24"},"For Masih hasn’t entered into holy places made with hands, which are representations of the true, but into heaven itself,\nnow to appear in the presence of Allah for us; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"HEB 9:25"},"nor yet that he should offer himself often, as the high priest enters into the holy place year by year with blood not his\nown, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"HEB 9:26"},"or else he must have suffered often since the foundation of the world. But now once at the end of the ages, he has been\nrevealed to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"HEB 9:27"},"Inasmuch as it is appointed for men to die once, and after this, judgement,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"HEB 9:28"},"so Masih also, having been offered once to bear the sins of many, will appear a second time, without sin, to those who\nare eagerly waiting for him for salvation. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"HEB 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 10:1"},"For the law, having a shadow of the good to come, not the very image of the things, can never with the same sacrifices\nyear by year, which they offer continually, make perfect those who draw near.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 10:2"},"Or else wouldn’t they have ceased to be offered, because the worshippers, having been once cleansed, would have had no\nmore consciousness of sins? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 10:3"},"But in those sacrifices there is a yearly reminder of sins.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 10:4"},"For it is impossible that the blood of bulls and goats should take away sins.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 10:5"},"Therefore when he comes into the world, he says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You didn’t desire sacrifice and offering, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but you prepared a body for me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 10:6"},"You had no pleasure in whole burnt offerings and sacrifices for sin.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 10:7"},"Then I said, ‘Behold, I have come (in the scroll of the book it is written of me)\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to do your will, O Allah.’”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 40:6-8"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 10:8"},"Previously saying, “Sacrifices and offerings and whole burnt offerings and sacrifices for sin you didn’t desire, neither\nhad pleasure in them” (those which are offered according to the law),\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 10:9"},"then he has said, “Behold, I have come to do your will.” He takes away the first, that he may establish the second,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 10:10"},"by which will we have been sanctified through the offering of the body of Al Masih Isa once for all.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 10:11"},"Every priest indeed stands day by day serving and often offering the same sacrifices which can never take away sins,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 10:12"},"but he, when he had offered one sacrifice for sins forever, sat down on the right hand of Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 10:13"},"from that time waiting until his enemies are made the footstool of his feet.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 10:14"},"For by one offering he has perfected forever those who are being sanctified.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 10:15"},"The Holy Spirit also testifies to us, for after saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 10:16"},"“This is the covenant that I will make with them: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘After those days,’ says the Lord, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘I will put my laws on their heart, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will also write them on their mind;’”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah\n31:33"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["then he says, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 10:17"},"“I will remember their sins and their iniquities no more.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 31:34"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 10:18"},"Now where remission of these is, there is no more offering for sin.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 10:19"},"Having therefore, brothers, boldness to enter into the holy place by the blood of Isa,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HEB 10:20"},"by the way which he dedicated for us, a new and living way, through the veil, that is to say, his flesh,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"HEB 10:21"},"and having a great priest over Allah’s house, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"HEB 10:22"},"let’s draw near with a true heart in fullness of faith, having our hearts sprinkled from an evil conscience, and having\nour body washed with pure water, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"HEB 10:23"},"let’s hold fast the confession of our hope without wavering; for he who promised is faithful.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"HEB 10:24"},"Let’s consider how to provoke one another to love and good works,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"HEB 10:25"},"not forsaking our own assembling together, as the custom of some is, but exhorting one another, and so much the more as\nyou see the Day approaching. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"HEB 10:26"},"For if we sin wilfully after we have received the knowledge of the truth, there remains no more a sacrifice for sins,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"HEB 10:27"},"but a certain fearful expectation of judgement, and a fierceness of fire which will devour the adversaries.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"HEB 10:28"},"A man who disregards Musa’s law dies without compassion on the word of two or three witnesses.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"HEB 10:29"},"How much worse punishment do you think he will be judged worthy of who has trodden under foot the Son of Allah, and has\ncounted the blood of the covenant with which he was sanctified an unholy thing, and has insulted the Spirit of grace?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"HEB 10:30"},"For we know him who said, “Vengeance belongs to me;” says the Lord, “I will\nrepay.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 32:35"]}],"caller":"+"}," Again, “The Lord will judge his\npeople.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 32:36; Zabur 135:14"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"HEB 10:31"},"It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living Allah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"HEB 10:32"},"But remember the former days, in which, after you were enlightened, you endured a great struggle with sufferings;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"HEB 10:33"},"partly, being exposed to both reproaches and oppressions; and partly, becoming partakers with those who were treated so.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"HEB 10:34"},"For you both had compassion on me in my chains, and joyfully accepted the plundering of your possessions, knowing that\nyou have for yourselves a better possession and an enduring one in the heavens.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"HEB 10:35"},"Therefore don’t throw away your boldness, which has a great reward.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"HEB 10:36"},"For you need endurance so that, having done the will of Allah, you may receive the promise.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"HEB 10:37"},"“In a very little while, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he who comes will come, and will not wait. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"HEB 10:38"},"But the righteous will live by faith. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["If he shrinks back, my soul has no pleasure in him.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["10:38\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Habakkuk 2:3-4"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"HEB 10:39"},"But we are not of those who shrink back to destruction, but of those who have faith to the saving of the soul.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"HEB 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 11:1"},"Now faith is assurance of things hoped for, proof of things not seen.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 11:2"},"For by this, the elders obtained testimony. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 11:3"},"By faith, we understand that the universe has been framed by the word of Allah, so that what is seen has not been made out\nof things which are visible. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 11:4"},"By faith, Habil offered to Allah a more excellent sacrifice than Qabil, through which he had testimony given to him that\nhe was righteous, Allah testifying with respect to his gifts; and through it he, being dead, still speaks.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 11:5"},"By faith, Enoch was taken away, so that he wouldn’t see death, and he was not found, because Allah translated him. For he\nhas had testimony given to him that before his translation he had been well pleasing to Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 11:6"},"Without faith it is impossible to be well pleasing to him, for he who comes to Allah must believe that he exists, and that\nhe is a rewarder of those who seek him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 11:7"},"By faith, Nuh, being warned about things not yet seen, moved with godly\nfear,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, reverence"]}],"caller":"+"}," prepared a ship for the saving of his house, through which he condemned the world, and\nbecame heir of the righteousness which is according to faith. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 11:8"},"By faith, Ibrahim, when he was called, obeyed to go out to the place which he was to receive for an inheritance. He went\nout, not knowing where he went. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 11:9"},"By faith, he lived as an alien in the land of promise, as in a land not his own, dwelling in tents with Isḥāq and Yaqub,\nthe heirs with him of the same promise. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 11:10"},"For he looked for the city which has the foundations, whose builder and maker is Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 11:11"},"By faith, even Sarah herself received power to conceive, and she bore a child when she was past age, since she counted\nhim faithful who had promised. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 11:12"},"Therefore as many as the stars of the sky in multitude, and as innumerable as the sand which is by the sea shore, were\nfathered by one man, and him as good as dead. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 11:13"},"These all died in faith, not having received the promises, but having\nseen",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “and being convinced of”"]}],"caller":"+"}," them and embraced them from afar, and having confessed that they\nwere strangers and pilgrims on the earth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 11:14"},"For those who say such things make it clear that they are seeking a country of their own.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 11:15"},"If indeed they had been thinking of that country from which they went out, they would have had enough time to return.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 11:16"},"But now they desire a better country, that is, a heavenly one. Therefore Allah is not ashamed of them, to be called their\nAllah, for he has prepared a city for them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 11:17"},"By faith, Ibrahim, being tested, offered up Isḥāq. Yes, he who had gladly received the promises was offering up his one\nand only son, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 11:18"},"to whom it was said, “Your offspring will be accounted as from Isḥāq,”\n",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["11:18 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Genesis 21:12"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 11:19"},"concluding that Allah is able to raise up even from the dead. Figuratively speaking, he also did receive him back from\nthe dead. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HEB 11:20"},"By faith, Isḥāq blessed Yaqub and Esau, even concerning things to come.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"HEB 11:21"},"By faith, Yaqub, when he was dying, blessed each of the sons of Yusuf, and worshipped, leaning on the top of his staff.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"HEB 11:22"},"By faith, Yusuf, when his end was near, made mention of the departure of the children of Israel, and gave instructions\nconcerning his bones. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"HEB 11:23"},"By faith, Musa, when he was born, was hidden for three months by his parents, because they saw that he was a beautiful\nchild, and they were not afraid of the king’s commandment. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"HEB 11:24"},"By faith, Musa, when he had grown up, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh’s daughter,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"HEB 11:25"},"choosing rather to share ill treatment with Allah’s people than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a time,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"HEB 11:26"},"considering the reproach of Masih greater riches than the treasures of Egypt; for he looked to the reward.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"HEB 11:27"},"By faith, he left Egypt, not fearing the wrath of the king; for he endured, as seeing him who is invisible.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"HEB 11:28"},"By faith, he kept the Passover, and the sprinkling of the blood, that the destroyer of the firstborn should not touch\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"HEB 11:29"},"By faith, they passed through the Red Sea as on dry land. When the Egyptians tried to do so, they were swallowed up.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"HEB 11:30"},"By faith, the walls of Jericho fell down, after they had been encircled for seven days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"HEB 11:31"},"By faith, Rahab the prostitute didn’t perish with those who were disobedient, having received the spies in peace.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"HEB 11:32"},"What more shall I say? For the time would fail me if I told of Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, Dawood, Samuel, and the\nprophets, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"HEB 11:33"},"who through faith subdued kingdoms, worked out righteousness, obtained promises, stopped the mouths of\nlions,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["11:33 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Daniel 6:22-23"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"HEB 11:34"},"quenched the power of fire,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["11:34 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Daniel 3:1-30"]}],"caller":"+"}," escaped the edge of the\nsword,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["11:34 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["1 Kings 19:1-3; 2 Kings 6:31–7:20"]}],"caller":"+"}," from weakness were made strong, grew mighty in war, and caused\nforeign armies to flee. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"HEB 11:35"},"Women received their dead by resurrection.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["11:35 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["1 Kings\n17:17-23; 2 Kings 4:32-37"]}],"caller":"+"}," Others were tortured, not accepting their deliverance, that they might obtain a better\nresurrection. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"HEB 11:36"},"Others were tried by mocking and scourging, yes, moreover by bonds and imprisonment.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"HEB 11:37"},"They were stoned.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["11:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Chronicles 24:20-21"]}],"caller":"+"}," They were sawn apart. They were tempted. They were slain\nwith the sword.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["11:37 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 26:20-23; 1 Kings 19:10"]}],"caller":"+"}," They went around in sheep skins and in goat skins; being\ndestitute, afflicted, ill-treated— \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"HEB 11:38"},"of whom the world was not worthy—wandering in deserts, mountains, caves, and the holes of the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"HEB 11:39"},"These all, having had testimony given to them through their faith, didn’t receive the promise,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"HEB 11:40"},"Allah having provided some better thing concerning us, so that apart from us they should not be made perfect.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"HEB 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 12:1"},"Therefore let’s also, seeing we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, lay aside every weight and the sin which\nso easily entangles us, and let’s run with perseverance the race that is set before us,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 12:2"},"looking to Isa, the author and perfecter of faith, who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising\nits shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 12:3"},"For consider him who has endured such contradiction of sinners against himself, that you don’t grow weary, fainting in\nyour souls. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 12:4"},"You have not yet resisted to blood, striving against sin. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 12:5"},"You have forgotten the exhortation which reasons with you as with children,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“My son, don’t take lightly the chastening of the Lord, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor faint when you are reproved by him; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 12:6"},"for whom the Lord loves, he disciplines, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and chastises every son whom he receives.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Proverbs\n3:11-12"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 12:7"},"It is for discipline that you endure. Allah deals with you as with children, for what son is there whom his father doesn’t\ndiscipline? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 12:8"},"But if you are without discipline, of which all have been made partakers, then you are illegitimate, and not children.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 12:9"},"Furthermore, we had the fathers of our flesh to chasten us, and we paid them respect. Shall we not much rather be in\nsubjection to the Father of spirits, and live? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 12:10"},"For they indeed, for a few days, punished us as seemed good to them; but he for our profit, that we may be partakers of\nhis holiness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 12:11"},"All chastening seems for the present to be not joyous but grievous; yet afterward it yields the peaceful fruit of\nrighteousness to those who have been trained by it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 12:12"},"Therefore lift up the hands that hang down and the feeble knees,\n",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 35:3"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 12:13"},"and make straight paths for your feet,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Proverbs\n4:26"]}],"caller":"+"}," so what is lame may not be dislocated, but rather be healed.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 12:14"},"Follow after peace with all men, and the sanctification without which no man will see the Lord,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 12:15"},"looking carefully lest there be any man who falls short of the grace of Allah, lest any root of bitterness springing up\ntrouble you, and many be defiled by it, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 12:16"},"lest there be any sexually immoral person, or profane person, like Esau, who sold his birthright for one meal.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 12:17"},"For you know that even when he afterward desired to inherit the blessing, he was rejected, for he found no place for a\nchange of mind though he sought it diligently with tears. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 12:18"},"For you have not come to a mountain that might be touched, and that burnt with fire, and to blackness, darkness, storm,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 12:19"},"the sound of a trumpet, and the voice of words; which those who heard it begged that not one more word should be spoken\nto them, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HEB 12:20"},"for they could not stand that which was commanded, “If even an animal touches the mountain, it shall be\nstoned”.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR adds “or shot with an arrow”"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 19:12-13"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"HEB 12:21"},"So fearful was the appearance that Musa said, “I am terrified and\ntrembling.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 9:19"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"HEB 12:22"},"But you have come to Mount Zion, and to the city of the living Allah, the heavenly Jerusalem, and to innumerable\nmultitudes of angels, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"HEB 12:23"},"to the festal gathering and assembly of the firstborn who are enrolled in heaven, to Allah the Judge of all, to the\nspirits of just men made perfect, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"HEB 12:24"},"to Isa, the mediator of a new covenant,",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah\n31:31"]}],"caller":"+"}," and to the blood of sprinkling that speaks better than that of Habil.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"HEB 12:25"},"See that you don’t refuse him who speaks. For if they didn’t escape when they refused him who warned on the earth, how\nmuch more will we not escape who turn away from him who warns from heaven,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"HEB 12:26"},"whose voice shook the earth then, but now he has promised, saying, “Yet once more I will shake not only the earth, but\nalso the heavens.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Haggai 2:6"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"HEB 12:27"},"This phrase, “Yet once more” signifies the removing of those things that are shaken, as of things that have been made,\nthat those things which are not shaken may remain. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"HEB 12:28"},"Therefore, receiving a Kingdom that can’t be shaken, let’s have grace, through which we serve Allah acceptably, with\nreverence and awe, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"HEB 12:29"},"for our Allah is a consuming fire.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["12:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy\n4:24"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"HEB 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"HEB 13:1"},"Let brotherly love continue. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"HEB 13:2"},"Don’t forget to show hospitality to strangers, for in doing so, some have entertained angels without knowing it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"HEB 13:3"},"Remember those who are in bonds, as bound with them, and those who are ill-treated, since you are also in the body.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"HEB 13:4"},"Let marriage be held in honour amongst all, and let the bed be undefiled; but Allah will judge the sexually immoral and\nadulterers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"HEB 13:5"},"Be free from the love of money, content with such things as you have, for he has said, “I will in no way leave you,\nneither will I in any way forsake you.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["13:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy\n31:6"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"HEB 13:6"},"So that with good courage we say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“The Lord is my helper. I will not fear. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["What can man do to me?”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["13:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 118:6-7"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"HEB 13:7"},"Remember your leaders, men who spoke to you the word of Allah, and considering the results of their conduct, imitate their\nfaith. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"HEB 13:8"},"Al Masih Isa is the same yesterday, today, and forever. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"HEB 13:9"},"Don’t be carried away by various and strange teachings, for it is good that the heart be established by grace, not by\nfood, through which those who were so occupied were not benefitted.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"HEB 13:10"},"We have an altar from which those who serve the holy tabernacle have no right to eat.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"HEB 13:11"},"For the bodies of those animals, whose blood is brought into the holy place by the high priest as an offering for sin,\nare burnt outside of the camp.",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["13:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 16:27"]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"HEB 13:12"},"Therefore Isa also, that he might sanctify the people through his own blood, suffered outside of the gate.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"HEB 13:13"},"Let’s therefore go out to him outside of the camp, bearing his reproach.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"HEB 13:14"},"For we don’t have here an enduring city, but we seek that which is to come.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"HEB 13:15"},"Through him, then, let’s offer up a sacrifice of praise to Allah\n",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["13:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Zabur 50:23"]}],"caller":"+"}," continually, that is, the fruit of lips which proclaim allegiance to his name.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"HEB 13:16"},"But don’t forget to be doing good and sharing, for with such sacrifices Allah is well pleased.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"HEB 13:17"},"Obey your leaders and submit to them, for they watch on behalf of your souls, as those who will give account, that they\nmay do this with joy, and not with groaning, for that would be unprofitable for you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"HEB 13:18"},"Pray for us, for we are persuaded that we have a good conscience, desiring to live honourably in all things.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"HEB 13:19"},"I strongly urge you to do this, that I may be restored to you sooner.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"HEB 13:20"},"Now may Allah of peace, who brought again from the dead the great shepherd of the sheep with the blood of an eternal\ncovenant, our Lord Isa, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"HEB 13:21"},"make you complete in every good work to do his will, working in you that which is well pleasing in his sight, through Al\nMasih Isa, to whom be the glory forever and ever. Amen. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"HEB 13:22"},"But I exhort you, brothers, endure the word of exhortation; for I have written to you in few words.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"HEB 13:23"},"Know that our brother Timothy has been freed, with whom, if he comes shortly, I will see you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"HEB 13:24"},"Greet all of your leaders and all the saints. The Italians greet you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"HEB 13:25"},"Grace be with you all. Amen. "]}]}